og:description:

Highlights Passing a percentage unit to the global abs() is deprecated since Dart Sass v1.65.0. It resulted in a deprecation warning when compiling Bootstrap with Dart Sass. This has been fixed internally by changing the values passed to the divide() function. The divide() function has not been fixed itself so that we can keep supporting node-sass cross-compatibility.

title: Limitations of Scoped CSS | Zell Liew
og:title: Limitations of Scoped CSS | Zell Liew
og:description:
I was really excited about Scoped CSS a couple of years back when frameworks like React and Vue introduced them.
As I began trying Scoped CSS out for myself, I was disappointed and I felt it didn't live up to its hype.
But after more tries, I'm happy to announce that Scoped CSS is indeed useful. You only have to realize what its limitations are and what to do when you face these limitations.
